I was just about to post the same thing. It was working in the last version (as far as I recall). When I installed the new version after the recent KSP update I can no longer fill stock tanks with just <abbr title="Liquid Fuel">LF</abbr>/LOX/<abbr title="Liquid Fuel">LF</abbr>+LOX. It only has the option to change the size of the tank.

I hope this can be resolved as I rely on having a full <abbr title="Liquid Fuel">LF</abbr> tank on some of my craft (some already in flight).

Cheers!

Small bug to report - on many if not all stock tanks where IFS allows for switching to xenon, resource amounts end up being 1 xenon per 1 unit of <abbr title="Liquid Fuel">LF</abbr>/OX volume in the tank originally. This is off by a factor of ~18-57 (depending on which stock parts we're supposed to take as models). For example: in the FLT100 (100 <abbr title="Liquid Fuel">LF</abbr>/OX volume), switching to xenon results in a tank that holds 100 xenon. It should hold about 5700 xenon going by the stock PB-750 (or whatever it's called).

My guess is that somewhere in the patches, the Xenon resource value was set to 1 \* the original <abbr title="Liquid Fuel">LF</abbr>/OX volume...
